Two parallel lines above this row of lotus panels. Frill swirly leaves and hibiscus or trumpet-like flowers within a row panel on the exterior under the rim. Base is beveled and partially glaze on the exterior of the footring, underneath and bottom of base are unglazed.

On the interior, row of classic scrolls between a single line underneath the rim and two paralle lines on the cavetto of the bowl. The center of the bowl contains two concentric circles within which is a bouquet of lotus flower, only the bottom half when the stalks/stems is visible. On the exterior, lower part of the body is decorated by a row of lotus panels and pearls. Underneath the everted rim, is a row of floral and leaf scrolls. Two sherds conjoined.
